> read neat page
"July 26th, 1710.

No luck again hunting but the Captain has discovered a most curious Statue the effects of which upon him are scarce to be believed; however if must be said the chief Effect so far as we are concerned is that the Small Beer which was supposed to last us through the Year is now gone in scarce a Week and still no Meat to be had.  Skinny John has said we ought to eat Rosie but the Captain would have none of it as she is akin to his Flesh and Blood and he set John to swabbing the Decks.   Anyway I am glad as I would not like to eat Rosie for she is a part of the Crew & would surely have not much meat anyway & also we have fruit."
> read torn page

> read torn page
"August 13, 1710

Whatever cruel force now animates Skinny John it is not the same one found in the Captain for his thirst is insatiable & his desperation fearsome.   Mad Old Jane said that this was his punishment for Treachery and Thieving from our own & the bastard killed her on the spot & drained her like a man drinking from a Wineskin.   Rosie has flown away.  I am playing the humble Servant but I know my Number is up & tonight I fly as well!"
> read crumpled page

> read crumpled page
"August 11, 1710

I fear the Captain has been foully Murdered, for he went fishing as usual (the way in watch he can catch a Fish now is a sight) but he has not let returned; however Skinny John who went sent to pick Fruit returned with far different demeanor & most damning he carried the same Witchery as was previously housed only in the Captain's person.  It is obvious to all what has befallen our beloved Captain & Cookie said as much.  Skinny John denies it but all but named himself Captain at once & the Captain's body not yet cold!   He says it was a Gift of the jungle which told him that he could find more such statues and become King of this place but I think he is Mad.  Cookie found drowned this evening & it looked like he had fallen in but of course that is more Tricks.   I am keeping one Eye on Rosie & one eye on my own Life."
> read yellowed page

> read yellowed page
"July 15th, 1710.

Those who survived the terrible storm were Myself and Rosie, Old Mad Jane, Skinny John, and Cookie.   Mister Edmund, Doxy Lu, and the new man (who I did not know well) are Drowned.  We feared the Captain lost overboard but found him clinging to the Hull and he laughed and said he that Captain Pisces would not die so Easily at such a little Drizzle.   However we are well and truly run aground and a good deal inland too.   We have fresh Water at least but not much Food left, must go hunting soon but such a place as this must be full of Beasts."
