Cavernous Cavemouth
You're standing at the foot of a mountain.  A looming black cave mouth leads north, into the heart of the mountain, while the trail south leads to the village.   Hot, wet, smelly air rolls from the cave mouth, making it seem like the maw of some enormous, horrible beast.

> n

> n
It's not that you're scared, exactly, it's just that something about that terrifying maw gives you a real case of Tapioca spine.   There's no way you're going in there!  At least, not without a little something to steady your nerves.
