Sauna of Kong
You're standing in a steamy volcanic cavern.    You can see sunlight from exits low in the wall to the south and high to the northwest.  The floor slopes downward towards a bubbling lava pit in the center of the room.    A gigantic ape sits by the edge of the pit, taking up most of the room.  He periodically shakes a dash of water from the jug he's carrying out into a wooden scoop and dashes it against the hot magma, sending up billowing clouds of steam that make everything look obscure and hazy.
You can see a gigantic ape and a lava pit.
> x ape

> x ape
A huge, tremendous, colossal, towering, Brobdignagian whopper of an ape.  He's so big he makes King Kong look like the Two of Kongs.   He's so enormous that not only does he sleep anywhere he wants, they bring him free room service in the morning and leave a mint on his pillow.  He's so gargantuan that the inside of this room, which is not small, is probably going to give him long-term back pain from alll the stooping over.  He's so ridiculously oversized that he could wrap his little toe in a black robe and send it to Halloween parties as Chief Justice of the Supreme Court William Howard Taft.

He's rather on the large size for an ape, is the general takeaway here.
> mimic ape

> mimic ape
As you focus on the ape, you feel your muscles bulge with raw strength.  You see yourself tumbling through the forest, trees snapping like twigs, your gnarled fists snatching up the heaviest boulders and logs and tossing them aside as if they were nothing.  You are now VERY strong.  Try to TAKE things that you couldn't before--you may be able to pick them up now, at least temporarily!
> x lava

> x lava
Bubbling lava oozes through cracks in the floor at the room's lowest point and pools in this hollow crater.
> drench lava

> drench lava
You douse the lava, sending up a huge cloud of steam.   The ape hoots in surprise and confusion as the vapor fills the room, temporarily blinding him.
> nw

> nw
You step out onto a path winding its way around the volcano.  You hear a strained squawk, and look up to see the parrot from before fluttering down to perch on a nearby outcropping.

Volcanic Path
This rocky path winds around the slope of the mountain.  It's a fairly easy trek, and the cool air here is refreshing.  A seemingly endless expanse of jungle stretches out to the west, but on the horizon, you spot the glint of polished glass and steel in the sunlight indicating far-off Gola City.

You can see a decrepit parrot.
> x city

> x city
It's fifty or sixty miles away, but without a way to make contact it might as well be on the other side of the solar sytem.  If only the plane had made it just a little further, you'd be in a classy restaurant by now, stuffing your face with sirloin stake and martinis on the company's dime, and getting ready to head out for a day of shopping before collapsing into a bubble bath.
You hear a lot less enraged hooting.  Sounds like the ape got the steam out of his eyes.
