Volcanic Peak
This is the caldera of the dormant volcano.   It's cooler up here, and the air is thin, but a few grasses and scrubs cling to the otherwise barren soil.   A faint path leads back to the southwest, over the ridge.

You can see a basalt idol.

Your head feels perfectly clear again.
> x idol

> x idol
A long, high-cheekboned face, carved out of black stone.  It seems frozen in the middle of some inhuman screech, its jaw opened wider than any living person's can stretch.  It's half buried in the ground, as if it's drowning in solid rock.  As with the other idols, something calls out to you, beckoning, begging you to TOUCH it.
> touch idol

> touch idol
As you touch the idol, your skin begins to itch, then crawl, then suddenly light up with sheets of searing pain.  In moments the pain passes, leaving only a stinging sensation and the feel of tremendous heat.  It's as if a massively powerful generator has just woken up in your belly.

The ground beneath you cracks, and molten magma oozes forth--and yet, the heat remains bearable, even as the liquid rock draws you down like quicksand.

Not only are you immune to fire, but you also now have the ability to HEAT objects in order to pour the power of the volcano into them!

But where exactly ARE you?

The Red Shrine
You're floating in a small bubble of open air far below the surface of the lava.   A few walls and pillars of black stone sketch out the blackened skeleton of a room, but even now the molten rock is oozing in to fill in the space.
You can see red hot lava.
> x lava

> x lava
