Ferny Overlook
The path ends at a cliff which runs from the northwest to the southeast.    From here, you can see a river rushing over the edge just south of you, pouring thousands of gallons of churning white water into a basin below.  To the southwest, where the river continues at a lower elevation, you spy an old ship run aground on a sandbar, near enough that you could glide over to it if you catch the wind just right.

