June 4th: Spanish ship ' Bailadora'.   No casualties.   Twenty pounds sterling; fine silverware; crate of wine.

June 21st: Freighter out of London 'Taurus'.  Fought to last man; sank.  Cargo unrecoverable (turned out to have been bouillon cubes).   Have been sailing through broth for last hour.

June 25th: Italian vessel, unnamed.  One casualty.   Fine art; gems; fish.

June 29th: English ship 'Marian May'.   No casualties.   Fifty pounds sterling; dozen bolts of linen; fine pistol; gold watch; face painting kit and patterns (kitty cat, skeleton)

July 3rd: French circus ship 'Circ Du Mer'.  No casualties.  Booty:  half-ton impractical costumery.   Three tons carnival tickets.  Troupe of trained monkeys.   Assured tickets good for shiny new penny-farthing if taken to Paris; costumery may be usable as fine napkins.  Monkeys to be released at next landfall.
