Riverbed
The river here is broad, shallow, and  slow-moving.    Sunlight filters down on you as you slip easily through the refreshingly cool water.    You see a few piranha, distant relatives of your friend in the tank, but they're smaller and less fond of fingers, and don't give you any trouble.   You can climb a wooden ramp to the north and board the Murdered Mermaid or swim east, into the deep basin of churning water under the waterfall.   To the west, the river narrows and rushes quickly over jagged rocks, making it impossible to safely swim in that direction.

