A Quaint Upper-Middle-Class Parisian Neighborhood
This is a small Paris cityscape made of grass and bamboo.  It's eerily empty, as far as you can see, and yet you feel like you're being watched from every window.    The road leads away to the southwest and to the north.   There's no Eiffel tower, but you can see a recreation of the Fontaine des Innocents, which burbles water from some underground spring, and a scale model of the Cathedral of Notre-Dame sits just to the side of the city center.  At the exact center of the city, in the bare patch of soil where the cathedral used to be, an open tunnel leads downwards.

You can see the Notre Dame Cathedral and the Fontaine des Innocents.
