> read inscription

> read inscription
NO JAM SESSIONS

Yes, we know it's fun to jam with the saints, but this organ is for use during services ONLY.   I have disassembled and scattered the activating mechanisms in order to prevent abuse.   Sister Boingboing's geologic survey has determined that a full-on killer jam could easily compromise the structural integrity of these tunnels.   If a little rocking out is worth the risk of a potential cave-in, then my grandmother is a dancing banana!

Signed, Brother Ooky
> drench tank

> drench tank
Your storm cloud fills the tank to the brim with water.
> heat tank

> heat tank
The cool water begins to bubble, then boil.    It begins to give off steam, which is drawn into the organ.
> play organ

> play organ
You pull the sheet music from one of your vest's inner pockets, unroll it, set it front of you, and plunk out a few notes on the tiny keys.   The steam-powered organ huffs into action, hooting and straining, the pipes reverberating.  The statues begin to vibrate, joining into on the raucous song you're banging out until the room is so full of ear-splitting noise you can barely stand it.   The floor shakes, and dust drifts down from the ceiling.  Suddenly, the floor beneath the organ collapses.  You jump back, just in time, as the entire massive contraption plummets with a moan into a much larger chamber under your feet.

Almost with a sigh, the statues stop their mad oscillation, and the spell fades.    It should now be possible to climb down into the chamber below.
