With a mighty heave and a few indelicate grunts, you deadlift the huge block of stone up over your head and back into the ceiling, pushing until you hear a click.  Then a snap.  Looks like you broke it, Muscles.

The hallway to the east is now open.
> e

> e
As you walk east, a pair of emerald eyes flash at you from out of the darkness.  Now, usually when someone says 'emerald eyes', it's a fancy way of saying 'green eyes'.  Not this time.  This pair of peepers are honest-to-god fist-sized emeralds.   They're peering at you from out of a large and quite lovely golden face, and that face belongs to a metal statue that's about thirty feet tall, assuming the half of her you can't see is proportional to the half you can.   She's standing waist-deep in a section of collapsed floor.

The metal lips part in a grin.  "Well, hi there, honey.  I THOUGHT I heard someone coming in through the back door.  It's been years since the last one, and he was such a bore.  I'm Vola the Unconquerable, you can call me Vola, and I'm afraid if you're looking for the idol you're a little late.  It's gone right out this mortal realm, gulp, gone forever."  She makes a zipping motion with her hand.  "Voop.  There it goes.   You see my last visitor was trying to make off with it -- not that I'm accusing you of anything kind that, savvy? -- and I chased him, and, well, down he went while he was still holding it."

She laughs, a hollow, booming sound.

"Also, I'm stuck in this pit now.  But I don't mind.  Kind of refreshing after six thousand years of sitting in the big room, you know?  Real change of pace.  I expect I'll get bored in a few decades or so and wriggle out and, oh, rain destruction on this and that, but for now, I'm all aces."   She folds her arms.  "Until then, you're free to make an offering, if you want.   Just make it good.  I'm pretty picky, you know."

